title: Ken Roczen wins Monster Energy Cup
text:
Home » News » Sports » Ken Roczen wins Monster… Ken Roczen wins Monster Energy Cup By The Associated Press October 18, 2015 1:09 am 
LAS VEGAS (AP) — Ken Roczen won the Monster Energy Cup on Saturday night at Sam Boyd Stadium. 
The Suzuki rider won the first and third main events and was fourth in the second. The 21-year0old German racer earned $100,000 in the supercross event. 
Red Bull KTM’s Ryan Dungey was second, finishing 2-5-2. Jason Anderson was third with 6-1-3 finishes. 
Kawasaki’s Austin Forkner took the Amateur All-Star Class championship, sweeping both main events. Kawasaki’s Lance Kobusch also swept both main events in the Supermini-Class. Topics:
